WEBVTT

00:05.539 --> 00:06.040
.

00:06.074 --> 00:06.974
- In the criminal justice
system,

00:08.142 --> 00:09.543
sexually based offenses

00:09.577 --> 00:11.479
are considered
especially heinous.

00:11.512 --> 00:14.115
In New York City,
the dedicated detectives

00:14.148 --> 00:15.783
who investigate
these vicious felonies

00:15.816 --> 00:17.385
are members of an elite squad

00:17.418 --> 00:19.553
known as
the Special Victims Unit.

00:19.587 --> 00:21.122
These are their stories.

00:21.155 --> 00:23.124
[dramatic musical flourish]

00:23.157 --> 00:24.592
- Good morning.

00:24.625 --> 00:26.394
Hello World, it's me, Mandy.

00:26.427 --> 00:29.163
It's Friday, September 8th,
and in case you can't tell,

00:29.197 --> 00:31.065
I'm actually excited to go
to school today.

00:31.099 --> 00:32.533
It's the fall pep rally.

00:32.566 --> 00:34.668
And the first thing is
to change.

00:34.702 --> 00:36.404
[chime]
That's better.

00:36.437 --> 00:38.539
I don't know why they interrupt
school to announce

00:38.572 --> 00:40.808
sports team, especially the
football players.

00:40.841 --> 00:42.643
It's like, "We get it.
You're popular."

00:43.411 --> 00:45.813
Also, the whole rah-rah
high school thing,

00:45.846 --> 00:47.348
everyone says it's suppose to

00:47.381 --> 00:49.117
be the best four years
of your life,

00:49.150 --> 00:51.085
you know, dances and parties
and romance.

00:51.119 --> 00:53.687
I like it but, I mean,
sometimes I wonder,

00:53.721 --> 00:55.356
you know, if I'm doing
it right.

00:55.389 --> 00:56.824
I've only been a sophomore
for a week.

00:56.857 --> 00:58.526
Hopefully this year will
be different.

00:58.559 --> 01:00.728
Hey, hey. It's Tuesday,
September 19th.

01:00.761 --> 01:03.464
The day the winners of the art
competition are announced.

01:03.497 --> 01:06.300
Oh, my gosh.
Look at my parents.

01:06.334 --> 01:08.869
- We want to wish you
good luck.

01:08.902 --> 01:10.704
- So embarrassing.

01:10.738 --> 01:12.706
Well, at least my parents
love me.

01:12.740 --> 01:14.408
But what I really want is

01:14.442 --> 01:15.576
to fall in love.

01:15.609 --> 01:17.278
What I don't get is how do
you know?

01:17.311 --> 01:18.479
Like, if you feel
like you're in love,

01:18.512 --> 01:20.314
does that mean you're
in love?

01:20.348 --> 01:21.682
Isn't love just a bunch of
chemicals swooshing

01:21.715 --> 01:23.184
around in your brain?

01:23.217 --> 01:24.685
My head hurts trying
to figure it out.

01:24.718 --> 01:26.454
Hello again, internet peeps.

01:26.487 --> 01:27.655
It's me, Mandy.

01:27.688 --> 01:29.557
I'm here with Stacey

01:29.590 --> 01:31.625
and Ashley.

01:31.659 --> 01:35.396
And the Sophomore Semi-Formal
is coming up and we need dates.

01:35.429 --> 01:36.864
[upbeat music playing]

01:36.897 --> 01:39.467
I think Stacey should go
with Mark.

01:39.500 --> 01:42.403
- Totally babe-soda,
but he'd never go with me.

01:42.436 --> 01:44.605
Maybe...
[sighs] Daniel.

01:44.638 --> 01:46.874
- No, I'm not going to.
She isn't that into me.

01:46.907 --> 01:48.442
- [chuckles]

01:48.476 --> 01:51.145
- Whoo, I could so see that.

01:51.179 --> 01:53.747
Then Mandy could go
with Andrew.

01:53.781 --> 01:57.251
- Uh, no way, guys,
he's like my brother.

01:57.951 --> 01:59.887
Hey, guys.
Say "hi", Andrew.

01:59.920 --> 02:01.622
- Hi.
[laughter]

02:01.655 --> 02:03.357
- These cool kids?
They're my crew.

02:03.391 --> 02:06.260
And this is
my fun, crazy life.

02:06.294 --> 02:07.895
Take six for the talent show.

02:07.928 --> 02:11.131
[Alessia Cara "Scars to Your
Beautiful" playing]

02:12.600 --> 02:16.637
* There's a hope that's
waiting for you in the dark *

02:16.670 --> 02:19.240
* You should know you're
beautiful *

02:19.273 --> 02:21.542
* Just the way you are
[cell phone dings]

02:21.575 --> 02:23.611
* And you don't have to change
a thing *

02:23.644 --> 02:25.446
- What are you doing
Saturday night?

02:25.479 --> 02:27.648
We just got invited to a party.

02:27.681 --> 02:29.750
Look.
[giggles]

02:29.783 --> 02:34.555
- That one text, it changed
everything.

02:37.925 --> 02:40.361
[sniffles] Hey, it's me.

02:40.394 --> 02:42.963
It's October, 16th.

02:42.996 --> 02:46.300
The worst day of my life.

02:46.334 --> 02:48.202
My reputation is ruined.

02:48.236 --> 02:49.670
And I'm done
with Wollman High,

02:49.703 --> 02:51.239
and I'm done
with my so-called friends.

02:51.272 --> 02:52.506
[mouse clicks]

02:52.540 --> 02:54.775
- When was the last time
you saw Mandy?

02:54.808 --> 02:56.577
- This morning at breakfast.

02:56.610 --> 02:58.512
She'd left for school at 8:00.
- And she never came back.

02:58.546 --> 03:00.448
We tried her cell, and it
went straight to voicemail.

03:00.481 --> 03:02.283
- And we called the school.
They said that she'd been

03:02.316 --> 03:04.685
in homeroom but not
in any classes after that.

03:04.718 --> 03:06.554
I checked her computer,

03:06.587 --> 03:08.622
found this.
- Uh, and Mrs. Fowler,

03:08.656 --> 03:11.659
you told 911 dispatch
that there were photos

03:11.692 --> 03:13.694
of a sexual nature.

03:13.727 --> 03:16.430
[tense music]

03:16.464 --> 03:19.567
- "Mandy is a grade-A slut."

03:19.600 --> 03:21.235
"Whore."

03:21.269 --> 03:22.903
"Skank-ass bitch."

03:22.936 --> 03:24.838
[scoffs]

03:24.872 --> 03:28.776
These were the nicer messages
that I woke up to yesterday.

03:28.809 --> 03:31.011
The rest are way worse.

03:31.044 --> 03:33.347
And this.

03:35.949 --> 03:38.752
Someone did this to me.

03:44.792 --> 03:47.495
Whoever did this,

03:47.528 --> 03:51.932
and you know who you are,

03:51.965 --> 03:54.668
please, just tell me why.

03:56.904 --> 03:59.340
Why.

04:05.379 --> 04:08.349
[dramatic music]

04:08.382 --> 04:15.589
*

04:52.393 --> 04:52.560
.

04:52.593 --> 04:53.260
- Please, just tell me why.

04:54.362 --> 04:55.796
- Mandy Fowler, 15,

04:55.829 --> 04:57.965
she posted this on her
blog this morning

04:57.998 --> 04:59.667
and then disappeared.

04:59.700 --> 05:02.336
The photo was being texted
by her classmates,

05:02.370 --> 05:04.505
and it was apparently taken
at a party on Saturday night.

05:04.538 --> 05:08.041
- So she's a victim
of cyberbullying, and worse.

05:08.075 --> 05:09.677
What else have we got?

05:09.710 --> 05:11.612
- Well, her last ping on her
cell was at 10:00

05:11.645 --> 05:13.481
this morning
from Wollman High.

05:13.514 --> 05:15.015
We're tracking her
cell phone records

05:15.048 --> 05:16.617
and contacting her friends,

05:16.650 --> 05:18.018
and of course she's active
on social media.

05:18.051 --> 05:19.620
- Okay.
- So we're going through

05:19.653 --> 05:21.389
all her accounts.
- And the parents are here?

05:21.422 --> 05:22.723
- Yeah and they seem loving,
supportive.

05:22.756 --> 05:24.858
There's no evidence
of family issues.

05:24.892 --> 05:26.494
Okay.
- Hey.

05:26.527 --> 05:27.661
Mandy hasn't used a debit or
credit cards.

05:27.695 --> 05:29.597
We got photos of her out at the

05:29.630 --> 05:31.365
subway stations, bus terminals.
[cell phone buzzing]

05:31.399 --> 05:32.900
- Okay, has she ever run away
before?

05:32.933 --> 05:34.602
- The parents say, "No."
She's a straight A student.

05:34.635 --> 05:36.036
She's got no trouble
with her peers.

05:36.069 --> 05:37.905
- Until this weekend.
- Hold on.

05:37.938 --> 05:39.106
TARU got her cell log.

05:39.139 --> 05:40.641
Before she powered down,

05:40.674 --> 05:42.410
she texted an Andrew Drake
ten times.

05:42.443 --> 05:44.044
- Can we get an address?
- Yeah. Upper West Side.

05:44.077 --> 05:45.446
That's two blocks
from the high school.

05:45.479 --> 05:46.614
I'm on it, Lieutenant.

05:46.647 --> 05:47.915
[both sigh]

05:47.948 --> 05:49.650
- Listen, I'm so sorry to drag
you back in here.

05:49.683 --> 05:51.385
I know you left early to be
with Noah--

05:51.419 --> 05:53.454
- No. You did the right thing.

05:53.487 --> 05:55.088
- Is everything okay at home?

05:55.122 --> 05:56.490
- Yeah.

05:56.524 --> 05:58.626
Yeah, all good. Let's, uh...

05:58.659 --> 06:00.594
Let's go talk to the parents.

06:02.563 --> 06:04.965
Mr. and Mrs. Fowler, I'm
Lieutenant Benson.

06:04.998 --> 06:06.400
- Did you find Mandy?

06:06.434 --> 06:08.168
- Not yet, but I can assure you

06:08.201 --> 06:10.070
that we're doing everything
we can.

06:10.103 --> 06:12.172
- I should have realized how
upset she was,

06:12.205 --> 06:13.474
made her talk to me.

06:13.507 --> 06:14.875
- After the party on Saturday?

06:14.908 --> 06:16.410
- She was...

06:16.444 --> 06:18.746
[sighs] so excited to go,
and..,

06:18.779 --> 06:20.648
What they did to her--I
just want to kill them.

06:20.681 --> 06:22.816
- Well, I can understand that.
So...

06:22.850 --> 06:25.085
do you know where this party
was and who was there?

06:25.118 --> 06:26.420
- At Daniel's.

06:26.454 --> 06:27.788
All Honors classmates.

06:27.821 --> 06:30.023
- Would she say anything
when she got home?

06:30.057 --> 06:31.559
- I fell asleep on the couch.

06:31.592 --> 06:33.193
When I check on her,
she was asleep.

06:33.226 --> 06:34.828
- Does Mandy have a boyfriend?

06:34.862 --> 06:36.129
Was she dating anyone?

06:36.163 --> 06:39.032
- No.
- Did she mention

06:39.066 --> 06:40.934
meeting someone online maybe?

06:40.968 --> 06:42.670
- No.

06:42.703 --> 06:45.606
Is this because of her vlog?

06:45.639 --> 06:47.441
We never should have
let her do that.

06:47.475 --> 06:48.876
- How could we stop her?
She...

06:48.909 --> 06:50.210
She was so proud of it.

06:50.243 --> 06:51.845
She had over
1,000 views last week.

06:51.879 --> 06:53.581
- Maybe one of those perverts
tracked her down.

06:53.614 --> 06:56.450
- You know, we're checking
into that.

06:56.484 --> 06:58.619
- And this Andrew Drake?

06:58.652 --> 07:00.754
Do you know if he was
at the party Saturday night?

07:00.788 --> 07:03.524
- Yes, but I can't imagine he'd
have anything to do with it.

07:03.557 --> 07:06.193
Mandy and Andrew were friends
since first grade.

07:07.528 --> 07:08.962
*

07:08.996 --> 07:10.864
- I swear, I don't know
where Mandy is.

07:10.898 --> 07:12.600
- Do you know
why she texted you

07:12.633 --> 07:14.034
ten times this morning?

07:14.067 --> 07:17.004
- No.
- No?

07:17.037 --> 07:19.940
You didn't read the texts?

07:19.973 --> 07:21.609
Okay.

07:21.642 --> 07:24.945
Listen, Andrew, I've been doing
this a long time,

07:24.978 --> 07:26.246
and I don't ask questions

07:26.279 --> 07:27.881
I don't already
know the answers to.

07:27.915 --> 07:29.983
- Okay, okay.

07:30.017 --> 07:31.685
She wanted to know why.

07:31.719 --> 07:33.053
The same thing she asked
in her vlog.

07:33.086 --> 07:34.855
- Andrew, what is this about?

07:34.888 --> 07:38.125
- Mrs. Drake, your son was
at a party where somebody...

07:38.158 --> 07:39.760
wrote some pretty awful things

07:39.793 --> 07:42.195
on an unconscious, half-naked
teenage girl.

07:42.229 --> 07:43.931
- What?
- Then they took a photo of it

07:43.964 --> 07:45.966
and texted it.
- I deleted that picture.

07:45.999 --> 07:47.000
- Well who took the photo?

07:47.034 --> 07:48.902
- I don't know.

07:48.936 --> 07:52.540
Everybody thinks that Mandy and
I are--are so tight,

07:52.573 --> 07:55.943
that I know what's going
on with her, but I don't.

07:55.976 --> 07:58.111
- What do you know, Andrew?

07:58.145 --> 08:00.013
- Mandy and her best friends.

08:00.047 --> 08:01.849
They gossip all the time.

08:01.882 --> 08:03.150
You should talk to them.

08:03.183 --> 08:04.652
- Any friend in particular?

08:04.685 --> 08:06.787
- Stacey Vanhoven,
Mandy's bestie.

08:06.820 --> 08:09.122
They had their heads together
all morning.

08:09.156 --> 08:11.291
Intense, like arguing.

08:11.324 --> 08:13.994
- Arguing about what?
- I don't know.

08:14.027 --> 08:16.096
But I heard Mandy say,

08:16.129 --> 08:19.032
"You aren't my friend anymore."

08:19.066 --> 08:20.768
[door knocks, opens]

08:20.801 --> 08:22.202
- Stacey.

08:22.235 --> 08:25.172
This detective wants to ask
you about Mandy Fowler.

08:25.205 --> 08:26.874
- Oh, my God, did you find her?

08:26.907 --> 08:30.110
- Not yet, but we would like
to ask you a few questions.

08:30.143 --> 08:31.945
- Yeah, um,

08:31.979 --> 08:33.113
Dad, I got this.

08:33.146 --> 08:35.015
- You sure?
- Yeah.

08:36.684 --> 08:38.986
- You and Mandy were pretty
close, right?

08:39.019 --> 08:41.154
- Yeah.

08:41.188 --> 08:43.824
Best friends since...
forever.

08:43.857 --> 08:45.626
- So it must have hurt
when she told you

08:45.659 --> 08:47.861
she didn't want to be
your friend anymore.

08:47.895 --> 08:50.063
[tense music]

08:50.097 --> 08:52.032
We know you two got
in a fight this morning.

08:52.065 --> 08:54.868
What was that about?
- I can't tell anyone.

08:54.902 --> 08:56.737
She said she would never talk
to me again.

08:56.770 --> 08:58.739
- Do you know who drew on her
on Saturday night?

08:58.772 --> 09:00.974
Who took the photo?
- No.

09:01.008 --> 09:03.143
I left the party early.
[sighs]

09:03.176 --> 09:04.845
- Then what do you know?

09:04.878 --> 09:08.616
*

09:08.649 --> 09:10.618
She's been humiliated.

09:10.651 --> 09:13.253
She's probably angry.
She's probably scared to death.

09:13.286 --> 09:14.788
She's out there all alone,

09:14.822 --> 09:17.224
and she could be
in serious trouble, Stacey.

09:17.257 --> 09:19.860
- [sighs]
She's not alone.

09:19.893 --> 09:22.295
- Who is she with?

09:22.329 --> 09:25.365
- [exhales]

09:25.398 --> 09:26.967
- Got something?
- Yeah, it turns out

09:27.000 --> 09:29.236
Mandy was in contact
with some guy online

09:29.269 --> 09:30.871
through ChatSlam.

09:30.904 --> 09:33.874
It was hidden behind an app
on her desktop

09:33.907 --> 09:35.275
which is why her parents
didn't know.

09:35.308 --> 09:36.977
- ChatSlam?
- Yeah.

09:37.010 --> 09:38.846
It's a social media
app, and it's untraceable.

09:38.879 --> 09:40.781
It deletes conversations
in seconds.

09:40.814 --> 09:42.983
- So Mandy didn't want a record
of whoever she was talking to.

09:43.016 --> 09:44.985
- So can we tell if it was one
of her vlog followers?

09:45.018 --> 09:46.286
- Well the only thing
I've got so far

09:46.319 --> 09:47.888
is that it was chat connection

09:47.921 --> 09:49.389
between her and
"Ethan E-ManWomanHatr"

09:49.422 --> 09:51.024
from Newark at 9:00 a.m.

09:51.058 --> 09:52.626
TARU's trying to recover
the conversation.

09:52.660 --> 09:53.894
[computer dings]

09:53.927 --> 09:56.129
Wait, hold up.

09:56.163 --> 09:57.965
Mandy's going live on Facebook.

09:57.998 --> 09:59.900
- TARU's tracing the social
media, right?

09:59.933 --> 10:02.770
- Yeah, yeah, all of them,
Instagram, YouTube, Twitter.

10:02.803 --> 10:05.906
- Carisi, SVU.
Mandy Fowler.

10:05.939 --> 10:07.941
Yeah, she's online right now.
- It's right there, go.

10:07.975 --> 10:10.678
[tense music]

10:10.711 --> 10:13.781
- It's me, Mandy.

10:13.814 --> 10:15.182
- Oh, my God, look at her.

10:15.215 --> 10:16.717
- To all of you haters
out there.

10:16.750 --> 10:17.851
I'm in a better place.

10:17.885 --> 10:19.252
- Okay, keep talking, honey.

10:19.286 --> 10:20.921
Let us figure out
where you are.

10:20.954 --> 10:22.189
Keep talking, keep talking.
- I'm better off

10:22.222 --> 10:23.857
without my fake friends.

10:23.891 --> 10:27.928
Their silence cuts deeper
than words.

10:27.961 --> 10:30.664
Mom, Dad,

10:30.698 --> 10:33.333
I'm sorry, I can't come back.

10:33.366 --> 10:35.268
- No, Mandy, hold on, hold on,
sweetie.

10:35.302 --> 10:36.269
Don't sign off.
- Goodbye.

10:36.303 --> 10:37.905
- TARU's got it.

10:37.938 --> 10:39.306
It's an IP address in Newark,
New Jersey.

10:39.339 --> 10:41.008
- Great work.

10:41.041 --> 10:43.677
*

10:43.711 --> 10:46.880
[sirens wailing]

10:55.789 --> 10:57.190
- The name on the account is
Ethan Cohen.

10:57.224 --> 10:59.727
It's apartment 223.
- This doesn't look good.

10:59.760 --> 11:01.729
[radio chatter]

11:01.762 --> 11:03.196
- NYPD, open up.

11:03.230 --> 11:04.364
[loud thuds]

11:04.397 --> 11:07.701
- Ethan, we have a warrant.

11:07.735 --> 11:08.969
Ethan Cohen.

11:09.002 --> 11:10.437
- Yeah?
- Open this gate.

11:10.470 --> 11:14.141
[dramatic music]

11:14.174 --> 11:15.709
- Where's Mandy Fowler?

11:15.743 --> 11:16.944
- I didn't do anything to her.
- Yeah.

11:16.977 --> 11:19.079
- Where is she?
- Mandy.

11:19.112 --> 11:20.380
- She's okay, she's fine.

11:20.413 --> 11:24.752
- Mandy. We're NYPD.
Are you okay?

11:24.785 --> 11:27.254
- Ethan, I trusted you.
- I didn't call the cops.

11:27.287 --> 11:29.823
- Mandy, it's okay, we're here
to take you home.

11:29.857 --> 11:31.491
- I'm not going with you.
I live here.

11:31.524 --> 11:34.261
- Sweetheart, you're 15 years
old, that's not gonna happen.

11:34.294 --> 11:36.363
Let's go.
- Just tell them, Mandy.

11:36.396 --> 11:39.366
- Tell us what?

11:39.399 --> 11:41.401
- That party...

11:41.434 --> 11:44.872
Those ass-hat high school boys.

11:44.905 --> 11:48.108
They did more than just draw
on her with a sharpie.

11:48.141 --> 11:50.343
*

11:50.377 --> 11:53.146
She was raped.

11:53.180 --> 11:57.918
*

12:02.055 --> 12:02.189
.

12:02.222 --> 12:02.823
- I couldn't tell my parents.

12:04.224 --> 12:06.126
They'd be so ashamed of me.

12:06.159 --> 12:08.996
- Mandy, your parents know
that this wasn't your fault.

12:09.029 --> 12:11.865
- You told Ethan
that you were raped?

12:11.899 --> 12:14.401
Can you help us understand
what happened?

12:14.434 --> 12:17.337
- I don't remember.

12:17.370 --> 12:19.339
I'd smoked a joint.

12:19.372 --> 12:22.209
I never do that.
- That's okay.

12:22.242 --> 12:24.544
That has nothing to do
with this.

12:24.577 --> 12:26.279
- [sniffles]

12:26.313 --> 12:29.082
The whole school thinks
that I'm a slut.

12:29.116 --> 12:31.284
[somber music]

12:31.318 --> 12:33.553
My reputation is ruined
forever.

12:33.586 --> 12:35.155
- Mandy, listen to me.

12:35.188 --> 12:37.324
We are gonna figure out
who did this to you,

12:37.357 --> 12:40.060
and we're going to help
you fight back.

12:40.093 --> 12:42.362
- I just want to know who,
and why.

12:42.395 --> 12:44.131
- Look.

12:44.164 --> 12:46.166
You smoked a joint so you were
a little high, right?

12:46.199 --> 12:48.401
Your memory's foggy,
that can happen.

12:48.435 --> 12:52.172
So why don't we--why don't we
start by you telling us

12:52.205 --> 12:56.343
